𝟒 𝐢𝐧 𝟏 𝐏𝐚𝐜𝐤 - Super useful AI tools for PhD students.

Literature review, diagrams, and paper writing - all gets covered.

Researcher.life offers 4 tools and more for PhD students.

Link: https://bit.ly/3JPx9Lq

How can these tools help you?

𝟏. 𝐑 𝐃𝐢𝐬𝐜𝐨𝐯𝐞𝐫𝐲

With R Discovery, you can identify papers for your literature review either via its website or mobile application. This tool will also keep you updated about the latest papers being published in your niche area.

𝟐. 𝐌𝐢𝐧𝐝 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐆𝐫𝐚𝐩𝐡

This tool offered by Researcher.life will help to easily draw very professional diagrams like graphical abstracts and infographics, etc. It offers tons of icons and templates that you can use in your diagrams.

𝟑. 𝐏𝐚𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐩𝐚𝐥

This tool can help you significantly in terms of paper writing. It will remove grammar and typo errors. It will also revise the text for you keeping the tone and meaning intact. You can also shorten the text with this tool.

𝟒. 𝐉𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐧𝐚𝐥 𝐅𝐢𝐧𝐝𝐞𝐫

If you are unsure which journal is the best fit for your manuscript, this tool will help you find the right journal based on your manuscript. You can also find papers for the related work section of your paper based on your manuscript.

What tools you use in your research?

Davis Smith, Founder of Cotopaxi, Shares 3 Lessons To Be Successful While Helping Others!

1. Don’t be fear-focused, even when sharks attack 🦈

2. Have trusted friends and mentors who can guide you 🤝

3. Find joy in discomfort and remember that the sun will rise again 🌅

For all the advice, watch the full video!

Davis is the founder and CEO of Cotopaxi, an outdoor gear brand with a humanitarian mission. He is a member of the United Nations Foundation's "Global Leadership Council" and a Presidential Leadership Scholar. Davis was Silicon Valley Community Foundation’s “CEO of the Year” in 2016 and previously started Brazil’s "Startup of the Year" in 2012. Davis holds an MBA from the Wharton School, an MA from the University of Pennsylvania, and a BA from Brigham Young University.

Smith is a serial entrepreneur with a passion for social enterprises. Prior to Cotopaxi, he co-founded PoolTables.com, the largest retailer of pool tables in the US. He later founded Baby.com.br, Brazil's Startup of the Year in 2012.

Born and raised in Latin America, Smith developed a passion for addressing poverty. He has a degree in International Studies from Brigham Young University, an MA in International Political Economy from the University of Pennsylvania, and an MBA from the Wharton School.

As a CEO, Smith emphasized the importance of giving back to the community and incorporated it as a central part of Cotopaxi's business model. Each Cotopaxi product carries a unique llama logo, symbolizing the company's commitment to poverty alleviation. Through its "Gear For Good" mission, Cotopaxi donates a percentage of its annual revenues to addressing poverty and supporting community development.

Perpetual Badejo (ACA, ACTI, FMVA®)Perpetual Badejo (ACA, ACTI, FMVA®) • 3rd+ • 3rd+ Bsc. Accounting(1st Class Hons🎖) | Tax specialist | Financial Analyst | Intrapreneur | Safety supervisorBsc. Accounting(1st Class Hons🎖) | Tax specialist | Financial Analyst | Intrapreneur | Safety supervisor
4d • 4d •
Dear Accountants, there is nothing as embarrassing as going for an interview and failing BASIC DOUBLE ENTRY questions, no excuse will ever be good enough!

As an Accountant, you need to understand that even though we live in a time where technology has automated a lot of our work process, it still doesn’t mean you should forget some of the basic foundations of Accounting, you should still be able to do your job perfectly with or without the Accounting software.

For instance there might be times when your Accounting system would have a glitch, but how would you even detect it when you don’t know the right entries that should have been passed, all you do is key data in and take whatever the system produces without vouching it.

While I understand that it’s very easy to get busy learning all of the big stuffs, but please once in a while take out time to refresh your memory on some of the basic things you have learnt a long time ago, you never can tell when that will come in handy.

And so for today, we’d just be refreshing our memory on this basic concept.

👉Concept A: Double entry for different classes of account.
🔘ASSET - Debit to Increase; Credit to Decrease
🔘LIABILITY- Credit to Increase; Dedit to Decrease
🔘INCOME - Credit to Increase; Debit to Decrease
🔘EXPENSES - Debit to Increase; Credit to Decrease

👉Concept B: Balances for different classes of Account
🔘Asset Account - Debit Balance
🔘Liability Account - Credit Balance
🔘Income Account - Credit Balance
🔘Expenses - Debit Balance

I hope this helps.
